                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> It depends on the situation.  The nice thing about Invoke (in zones where they haven't "fixed" pathing or where adds are not a problem) is its longer duration...and its shorter cast time.  At 36, you should have pretty decent specialization and alteration skills so I find it hard to believe you fizzle THAT much..).<br /><br />However, with the implementation of pathing changes or where you need to keep the mob controlled, regular fear is a quite viable option and many of us use regular vs invoke, for example, in the planes where (1) the mobs are unfearable or (2) you don't want them going too far away.  Sounds like OT is about the same (although, frankly, I used invoke but I was also hunting druids in WC at your level...not sure why you're not =P).<br /><br />Invoke fear always felt like it was harder to resist and always lasted the same duration vs regular breaking early but I was never able to "prove" that...</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
