                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> In regards to the OT (No, I never di the WC Druids, was told about them, but not before I reached lvl 45ish, and felt it would be a waste of time, when I now had other areas I was enjoying hunting):  I used invoke fear, and never found problems of mobs not coming after me again. . .  My way of doing it was to have my pet set as "guard" in my pulling spot (usually along the wall south of the fort, far enough from the gargoyl guard not to get them agroing and KSing me).  I would then run out, find whatever mob I wanted to pull, and cast darkness on it.  If it was resisted (which at lvl 29, when I started soloing these red mobs, it did about one in three or four times) I would run past the gargoyle guards, through the tunnel, and into the fort.  Agro was rarely held long enough to get the mob through, the guards usually did a good job of saving me.  If not, I would FD, and they guards would still save me.  If I was lucky and had SoW, it made this easier, but is still possible, I never pulled from TOO far out.  When darkness held, I would run a ways away, until it was safe to stop and cast a DoT (takes practise to know when you are far enough out that it won't get you before the spell goes off, but not so far that you are out of range, although going to far is preferable to not, they will catch up to you.)  I found that my main DoT would always wear off shortly before darkness, so if I needed to recast, as soon as the DoT wore off, I recast darkness, then the DoT.  I would run to my pet, then, and, depending on how far away the mod was, sometimes get another DoT off before.  At this point, I usually had solid agro, my pet wouldn't take it from me.  I sent pet in, and just before the mob got to me, I would fear it (Using Invoke Fear, once I had it.)  Then I sat down and waited.  Unless killed by guards, or my DoTs (as happened occasionally) did NOT out damage my pet, the mob would come back no matter how far he ran, as darkness kept him close enough not to loose agro, but well enough away that I was totally safe.  Invoke Fear was my choice here as it DID last long, allowed the mob to get father, my pet and DoTs to do more damage, and make it safe for me to med.  Usuallly I would have to fear and darkness once more before I killed the mob, unless I wanted't waste mana by nuking the sucker to oblivion, but I would often (using KEI at those lvls, before the KEI nerf) be able to keep my mana about the same lvl, always ready to fight again as soon as the mob went down.  For fun, I also maxed my 1HB skills here, following my pet and the mob when feared and hitting it, when I got bored of sitting.<br /><br />Just my take on it, invoke fear is, in my opinion, the optimal fear spell.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
