                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Markkos, my normal method of killing is to start out fear kiting, then change to another style if fearing doesn't work.  I don't root/rot unless there isn't another way to kill mobs.  I've played my druid to level 62 and don't care to root/rot anymore.  That's not saying I wouldn't use that method; its just not one of my favorites anymore.  I find I don't tank my pet, unless the area I'm in doesn't lend itself to fear or aggro kiting.  Good example for me was the Dulak Harbor tunnels.  When I was fighting in there to get my Comatose spell, I found the mobs were spaced too close together to kite, so I used my 49 pet and pet tanked them.  My offense, defense, and weapons skills are maxxed, so don't have a good reason to tank.  I normally keep manaskin up and try not to get hit on easy mobs like cyclops.  Saves me a peridot.  A lot of the things I do while fighting and the buffs I use are by habit and not necessarily the most efficient way.  That's why I read these boards.  I get a lot of good info from other necros.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
