                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> First of all why use Manaskin (and therefore, a Peridot) when you can just Bond of Death it and shrug off about 40%+ of the damage it does to you.  Invoke Fear has a -20 Resist Adjust (check Lucy), so it's less resisted.  I don't know why you're using Fear.  I hunted in The Overthere from level 34 - 39 (then WC Rangers/Druids from 39 to 41, then DL Skellies from 41 - 44, SolB Grouped from 44 - 47, then Spirocs in TD from 47 - 51 [UBER EXP HERE, 2 NIGHTS 4 LEVELS] just to give you a tip on where to hunt hehe).<br /><br />Anyways, when I hunted in The Overthere, I always used Invoke Fear.  Fact and matter is, all your spells should be cast on the mob while it is in range.  You may want to consider doing this;<br /><br />-  Pull with Dooming Darkness<br />-  Invoke Fear<br />-  Sic Pet<br />-  Boil Blood<br />-  Vampiric Curse (Counter Call of Bones health drain)<br />-  Run ahead of it a few feet (hardly no adds here)<br />-  Sit Down<br />-  Get up and re-Invoke Fear as necessary<br /><br />Fear sucks, and after I dinged 34, I have never used it since.  The level 4 fear is the only fear spell without a resist adjust so it's also more resistable.  A resisted Snare followed by a resisted Fear = Dead Necro if you don't have FD up (which I usually didn't).</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
